      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAROLINE BANNER (7) was in the minors two back (23.40) at Richmond but ran below best last time there, finishing 7th. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of three starts. Key runner on her best form. ZIPPING PERCAT (1) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage third, beaten 9 lengths (30.70) at Gosford in a Mix over 515m. The form out of last race has been strong. Leading chance. MAJOR FORTE (8) has been in the minor money at both career runs, the latest finishing third (18.10) at Taree Super Track. Bold showing expected again. TURN UP ACE (6) makes debut for the Craig Blakemore kennel. Market should provide a lead to his ability.",
